When I was a kid, my alarm-clock was usually my dad writing songs on the piano in the living room and my mom practising her concert solo in the bathroom. My dream was to be a musician like them. Their exact words to that were ‚Äò‚Äôbeing an artist is too complicated, DON‚ÄôT DO MUSIC‚Äô‚Äô! So I lived all my teenage years writing songs in secret, thinking it would take me nowhere and I went on different journeys. It was only 2 and half years ago that I realised life happens ONE TIME. That if you‚Äôre not gonna try ‚Äò‚Äôcomplicated‚Äô‚Äô, it isn‚Äôt worth living.
So ladies and gentlemen, I am my parents‚Äô HƒíIR. And this is THREADS, my first single of my debut E.P.  THREADS is an ode to generational love, to that fine line that separates reality and dreams‚Ä¶ It‚Äôs about how beautiful, unpredictable and fucked up love is. This is me pouring my heart out for the first time. Me being myself for the very first time. This is a FIRST. There will be a second single and a third and hopefully hundreds more. But nothing will feel like this VERY FIRST TIME. I am proud to say the 2 geniuses I built the HƒíIR sound with are @jabhol and @jeevsingh100. For 2 years, it was just us in any room, uber or instrument we‚Äôd find to create music with. Last but not least, thank you @peter_mayes for taking THREADS to the next level, and @andreamarcaccini for this beautiful artwork. And the biggest THANK YOU goes to my team for believing in my dreams even more than I do. Now let‚Äôs pop some champagne cause WEEEEE FKIN DID THIS. ü•Ç üçæ Song link in bio
